						               													<description>In Hand Circus', you look at the mission card and use the components and your hand to perform a show as requested. Whoever performs it last gets a blue ball from the circus master as they need more practice&amp;#10;&amp;#10;A flashy circus performs by hand!&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Game Setup&amp;#10;(1) Each player takes one of each red, yellow, and green disc, a hat, a tiger, an elephant, and a stick.&amp;#10;(2) Shuffle the cards and make a facedown pile in the center of the table and set the audience pieces as many as one less than the number of players near the card deck. &amp;#10;(3) Set 12 blue discs next to the card deck.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Game Play &amp;#10;&amp;#10;     The red band is there to indicate the thumb.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;#10;(1) Someone reveals a card from the deck, and then everyone starts to perform the show which is shown on the card. &amp;#10;(2) Fulfill the mission and take the audience. When all the audiences are gone, check if players have performed correctly. &amp;#10;&amp;#10;     If a player incorrectly performed a show, the player has to return the audience piece. Then the players who have no audience perform again to win the audience. &amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;#10;(3) When a round ends, the player with no audience piece gets a blue disc.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;End of the Game &amp;#10;Each blue disc is -1 point. Anytime during the game, if a player gets the specific amount of the blue discs, the player is eliminated from the game. (For a 4-player game: 4 discs, 3-player: 5 discs, 2-player: 6 discs) &amp;#10;&amp;#10;     Remove the audience piece as the player gets eliminated. &amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Play until one player remains. The player wins the game.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
